ench Grand Prix]]\n| 24,148\n|-\n| '''[[List of Formula One driver records#Total fastest laps|Most fastest laps]]'''\n| [[2001 Australian Grand Prix]]\n| 77\n|-\n| '''[[List of Formula One driver records#Most fastest laps in a season|Most fastest laps in a season]]'''\n| {{F1|2004}}<ref group=\"N\">Record shared with [[Kimi R\u00e4ikk\u00f6nen]] ({{F1|2005}} and {{F1|2008}}).</ref>\n| 10\n|-\n| '''[[List of Formula One driver records#Pole, win and fastest lap in same race|Most hat-tricks (pole, win and fastest lap)]]'''\n| [[2002 Japanese Grand Prix]]\n| 22\n|-\n| '''[[List of Formula One driver records#Pole, win and fastest lap in same race|Most hat-tricks in a season]]'''<ref>{{cite web|title=5 hat tricks in a season|url=http://en.espn.co.uk/f1/motorsport/driver/1146.html|publisher=ESPN|accessdate=13 May 2015}}</ref>\n| {{F1|2004}}<ref group=\"N\">Record shared with [[Alberto Ascari]] in {{F1|1952}}.</ref>\n| 5\n|-\n| '''[[List of Formula One driver records#Most races with a single constructor|Most races with a single constructor]]'''\n| [[2005 European Grand Prix]]\n| 181\n|}\n;Footnotes:\n{{Reflist|group=N}}\n\n== Books and films ==\n* {{Cite book | last = Allen | first = James | authorlink = James Allen (journalist) | title = Michael Schumacher: Driven to Extremes | publisher = Bantam Books | year = 1999 | isbn = 978-0-553-81214-5 | url-access = registration | url = https://archive.org/details/michaelschumache0000alle }}\n* {{Cite book | last = Allen | first = James | title = Edge of Greatness | publisher=Headline |year=2007 | isbn = 978-0-7553-1678-6 }}\n* {{Cite book | last = Collings | first = Timothy | title = The Piranha Club | publisher=Virgin Books|year=2004 | isbn = 978-0-7535-0965-4}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Collings| first = Timothy | title = Team Schumacher | publisher=Highdown |year=2005 | isbn = 978-1-905156-03-0}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Domenjoz | first = Luc | title = Michael Schumacher: Rise of a genius |year=2002 | publisher=Parragon | isbn = 978-0-7525-9228-2}}\n* {{Cite book | last =Henry | first =Alan (ed.) | authorlink = Alan Henry | title =Autocourse 1992\u201393 | publisher=Hazleton Publishing |year=1992 | isbn = 978-0-905138-96-1}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Henry | first = Alan | title = Wheel to Wheel: Great Duels of Formula One Racing |year=1996 | publisher=Weidenfeld Nicolson Illustrated | isbn = 978-0-7538-0522-0}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Hilton | first = Christopher | title = Michael Schumacher: The greatest of all | publisher=Haynes |year=2003 | isbn = 978-1-84425-044-8}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Hilton | first = Christopher | title = Michael Schumacher: The Whole Story | publisher=Haynes |year=2006 | isbn = 978-1-84425-008-0}}\n* {{Cite book | last =Kehm | first =Sabine | title =Michael Schumacher. Driving Force | publisher=Random House |year=2003 | isbn = 978-0-09-189435-1}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Matchett | first = Steve | authorlink = Steve Matchett | year=1995 | title=Life in the Fast Lane: The Story of the Benetton Grand Prix Year | isbn=978-0-297-81610-2 | publisher=Weidenfeld and Nicolson | location = London}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Matchett | first = Steve | year=1999 | title=The Mechanic's Tale: Life in the Pit Lanes of Formula One | isbn=978-0-7603-0754-0 | publisher=MBI Pub. | location = Osceola, Wisconsin}}\n* {{Cite book | last = Williams | first = Richard| title = The Death of Ayrton Senna | publisher=Bloomsbury|year=1999 | isbn = 978-0-7475-4495-1}}\n\nSchumacher had a voice role in the [[Disney]]/[[Pixar]] film ''[[Cars (film)|Cars]]''. His character is himself as a [[Ferrari F430]] who visits Radiator Springs to get new tires from Luigi and Guido at the recommendation of Lightning McQueen. During arrival, Luigi and Guido both faint in excitement when they see him. The French film ''[[Asterix at the Olympic Games (film)|Asterix and Obelix at the Olympic Games]]'' features Schumacher in a cameo role as a chariot driver called Schumix.\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of Formula One