{"title_page": "Stokesley Sports Club F.C.", "text_new": "{{Infobox football club\n| image    = Stokesley Sports Club F.C. logo.png\n| image_size = 160px\n| clubname = Stokesley Sports Club\n| fullname = Stokesley Sports Club Football Club\n| nickname = Stowsla\n| founded  = 1920\n| ground   = Stokesley Sports Club, [[Stokesley]]\n| capacity = 2,000\n| chairman = Eric Taylor\n| manager  = Steve Todd\n| league   = {{English football updater|StokesSC}}\n| season   = {{English football updater|StokesSC2}}\n| position = {{English football updater|StokesSC3}}\n|  pattern_la1=_black_stripes|pattern_b1=_blackstripes_thin4|pattern_ra1=_black_stripes|pattern_so1=_2 white stripes|     leftarm1=FF0000|body1=FF0000|rightarm1=FF0000|shorts1=000000|socks1=000000|\n}}\n\n'''Stokesley Sports Club Football Club''' is a [[association football|football]] club based in [[Stokesley]], [[North Yorkshire]], England. They are currently members of the {{English football updater|StokesSC}} and play at the Stokesley Sports Club.\n\n==History==\nFormed in 1920, the club spent most of the 20th century participating in local leagues before joining the [[Teesside Football League|Teesside League]] in 1994 before progressing to the [[Wearside League]] in 1999. Seven years later the club was accepted into the [[Northern League (football)|Northern League]].<ref>[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/stokesleysportsclub/a/club-history-25813.html Club website history page]</ref>\n\nIn each of their first two seasons at the higher level, Stokesley finished near the middle of the table. Promotion has also enabled the club to participate in national competitions - in the [[FA Vase]] their best performance came in 2008\u201309 when they reached the Second Round, and during the same season they made their debut in the [[FA Cup]], beating [[Washington F.C.|Washington]] in the Extra Preliminary Round before losing to [[Wakefield F.C.|Wakefield]] in the Preliminary Round.\n\nIn the summer of 2009 the club changed their name to Stokesley Football Club.\n\nIn 2009\u201310 the club became champions of the Northern League Second Division and gained promotion to the First Division for the first time in the club's history.  They scored in every league game and had the league's top scorer in Andrew Jennings.\n\nIn 2009 the club's under-13 team won the national [[Tesco Cup]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090713010147/http://www.tesco-u13-cup.com/newsDetail.asp?id=48 Tesco Cup]</ref>\n\nIn season 2010\u201311 the club finished 16th in division 1, but following the season the manager, chairman and secretary as well as the rest of the committee resigned quoting a lack of support from the sports club.  Renamed Stokesley Sports Club FC, in 2011, a new team was appointed under the leadership of manager Monty Alexander. In the 2011\u201312 season Stokesley were relegated back to Division Two after finishing the season with 4 points and not having won a single game.\n\nIn the 2015-16 season, Stokesley were relegated into the [[Wearside League]]. Despite ending the season on a high, winning two of their final three games, Stokesley finished on 14 points, collecting just a single point away from home, finishing bottom of the table.  Season 2018-19 saw the Wearside League and the abandoned Teesside League combine and reform into two new leagues - the Wearside League and the North Riding League.  Stokesley joined the North Riding League Premier Division.  A new manager was employed in season 2019-20, Steve Todd who had just brought his team up from Division One.\n\n==Honours==\n*'''[[Northern Football League]] Division Two'''<ref name=\"FCHD\">{{Fchd|id=STOKESLE|name=Stokesley}}</ref>\n**Champions 2009\u201310\n*'''[[Wearside League]]'''<ref name=\"FCHD2\">{{Fchd|id=STOKESSC|name=Stokesley Sports Club}}</ref>\n**Runners-up 2005\u201306\n*'''Wearside League Division Two'''\n**Runners-up 1999\u20132000\n\n==Records==\n*'''[[FA Cup]]'''<ref name=\"FCHD\"/><ref name=\"FCHD2\"/>\n**Preliminary Round 2008\u201309, 2009\u201310\n*'''[[FA Vase]]'''\n**Second Round 2008\u201309, 2010\u201311\n\n==Players==\n\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n{{Official website|http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/stokesleysportsclub/}}\n\n\n{{coord|54|28|04.79|N|1|10|42.29|W|region:GB_type:landmark|display=title}}\n\n[[Category:Football clubs in England]]\n[[Category:Football clubs in North Yorkshire]]\n[[Category:Association football clubs established in 1920]]\n[[Category:1920 establishments in England]]\n[[Category:Stokesley]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox football club\n| image    = Stokesley Sports Club F.C. logo.png\n| image_size = 160px\n| clubname = Stokesley Sports Club\n| fullname = Stokesley Sports Club Football Club\n| nickname = Stowsla\n| founded  = 1920\n| ground   = Stokesley Sports Club, [[Stokesley]]\n| capacity = 2,000\n| chairman = Eric Taylor\n| manager  = Steve Todd\n| league   = {{English football updater|StokesSC}}\n| season   = {{English football updater|StokesSC2}}\n| position = {{English football updater|StokesSC3}}\n|  pattern_la1=_black_stripes|pattern_b1=_blackstripes_thin4|pattern_ra1=_black_stripes|pattern_so1=_2 white stripes|     leftarm1=FF0000|body1=FF0000|rightarm1=FF0000|shorts1=000000|socks1=000000|\n}}\n\n'''Stokesley Sports Club Football Club''' is a [[association football|football]] club based in [[Stokesley]], [[North Yorkshire]], England. They are currently members of the {{English football updater|StokesSC}} and play at the Stokesley Sports Club.\n\n==History==\nFormed in 1920, the club spent most of the 20th century participating in local leagues before joining the [[Teesside Football League|Teesside League]] in 1994 before progressing to the [[Wearside League]] in 1999. Seven years later the club was accepted into the [[Northern League (football)|Northern League]].<ref>[http://www.pitchero.com/clubs/stokesleysportsclub/a/club-history-25813.html Club website history page]</ref>\n\nIn each of their first two seasons at the higher level, Stokesley finished near the middle of the table. Promotion has also enabled the club to participate in national competitions - in the [[FA Vase]] their best performance came in 2008\u201309 when they reached the Second Round, and during the same season they made their debut in the [[FA Cup]], beating [[Washington F.C.|Washington]] in the Extra Preliminary Round before losing to [[Wakefield F.C.|Wakefield]] in the Preliminary Round.\n\nIn the summer of 2009 the club changed their name to Stokesley Football Club.\n\nIn 2009\u201310 the club became champions of the Northern League Second Division and gained promotion to the First Division for the first time in the club's history.  They scored in every league game and had the league's top scorer in Andrew Jennings.\n\nIn 2009 the club's under-13 team won the national [[Tesco Cup]].<ref>[https://web.archive.org/web/20090713010147/http://www.tesco-u13-cup.com/newsDetail.asp?id=48 Tesco Cup]</ref>\n\nIn season 2010\u201311 the club finished 16th in division 1, but following the season the manager, chairman and secretary as well as the rest of the committee resigned quoting a lack of support from the sports club.  Renamed Stokesley Sports Club FC, in 2011, a new team was appointed under the leadership of manager Monty Alexander. In the 2011\u201312 season Stokesley were relegated back to Division Two after finishing the season with 4 points and not having won a single game.\n\nIn the 2015-16 season, Stokesley were relegated into the [[Wearside League]]. Despite ending the season on a high, winning two of their final three games, Stokesley finished on 14 points, collecting just a single point away from home, finishing bottom of the table.  Season 2018-19 saw the Wearside League and the abandoned Teesside League combine and reform into two new leagues - the Wearside League and the North Riding League.  Stokesley joined the North Riding League Premier Division.  A new manager was employed in season 2019-20, Steve Todd who had just brought his team up from Division One.\n\n==Honours==\n*'''[[Northern Football League]] Division Two'''<ref name=\"FCHD\">{{Fchd|id=STOKESLE|name=Stokesley}}</ref>\n**Champions 2009\u201310\n*'''[[Wearside League]]'''<ref name=\"FCHD2\">{{Fchd|id=STOKESSC|name=Stokesley Sports Club}}</ref>\n**Runners-up 2005\u201306\n*'''Wearside League Division Two'''\n**Runners-up 1999\u20132000\n\n==Records==\n*'''[[FA Cup]]'''<ref name=\"FCHD\"/><ref name=\"FCHD2\"/>\n**Preliminary Round 2008\u201309, 2009\u201310\n*'''[[FA Vase]]'''\n**Second Round 2008\u201309, 2010\u201311\n\n==Players==\n\n===Current squad===\n{{fs start}}\n{{Fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=GK |name=Lewis Shaw}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=GK |name=Andrew Jowett}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Tim Sharples}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Phillip Watson}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Kai Matthews}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Craig Winter}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Rhys Tapner}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Michael Graham}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Seb Hanratty}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=DF |name=Sean Davies}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Billy McGrath}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Daniel Jones}}\n{{fs mid}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Connor Hardman}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Craig Hill}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Tom Carney}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Chris Lynas}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Abdul Wahas}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Jake Laverick}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=MF |name=Adam Jones}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=FW |name=Ryan Rivis}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=FW |name=Shaun Laverick}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=FW |name=Daniel Joseph}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=FW |name=Anthony Barnes}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=FW |name=Sean Oddy}}\n{{fs player|  |nat=ENG |pos=FW |name=Marcus Allen}}\n{{fs end}}\n\n==References=